1
00:00:14,767 --> 00:00:18,033
Oh, our visitors
have arrived, baby.

2
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:18,867
Chloe!

3
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,100
Don't you dare come near, Eden!

4
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,433
You're not what I want.

5
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:27,067
Give Amanda to me, or else
you won't see your child.

6
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,067
Rina!

7
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,067
I'm here now.
I'm coming with you.

8
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,067
Mom, no!

9
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,067
Don't try to intervene, Eden.

10
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,300
Mom, please.

11
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:37,133
No one else should get hurt.
You can be free again.

12
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:38,267
Me?

13
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,000
I will be running all my life

14
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:41,767
because the police will hunt
for me.

15
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:44,367
But you know what? I don't mind.

16
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,733
As long as I get my revenge
for Angelo.

17
00:00:46,867 --> 00:00:48,567
Lord, first of all,

18
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:53,467
I want to thank you
for keeping Eden's baby safe.

19
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:56,767
But the child's life
is in danger again.

20
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,467
I won't let you win, Rina.

21
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,133
I'm not going to run away.

22
00:01:00,267 --> 00:01:01,167
Run, Amanda!

23
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:03,267
Our baby!

24
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:04,400
Lucho!

25
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:05,733
The baby.

26
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:10,533
The baby might get hurt!

27
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:14,967
Lucho!

28
00:01:27,133 --> 00:01:28,467
Lucho!

29
00:01:33,567 --> 00:01:35,200
Don't hurt my mom!

30
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:36,800
No!

31
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,300
Let go of my mom!

32
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:39,600
Let's see what you can do.

33
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:40,933
Can you pull the trigger?
Put that down!

34
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:42,733
I can!

35
00:01:42,867 --> 00:01:44,767
- Are you sure?
- Put the gun down!

36
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:47,733
Don't make your hands dirty.
Put the gun down.

37
00:01:47,867 --> 00:01:49,067
Go to your baby.

38
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:51,400
I knew you couldn't do it.
Put the gun down!

39
00:01:58,467 --> 00:01:59,400
Yen!

40
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:01,667
Yen! Stay here.

41
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:03,233
Stay here. Just stay here
with the baby.

42
00:02:03,367 --> 00:02:04,667
Red and I will look for them.

43
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,033
I can't, Uncle.

44
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:09,233
I have to be a good daughter
before I can be a good mother.

45
00:02:09,367 --> 00:02:10,733
I can't forgive myself

46
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:12,900
if something bad happens
to my mom.

47
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:15,200
I'll take care of Yenyen.

48
00:02:15,367 --> 00:02:16,967
I'll try to talk to my mom.

49
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,733
I might change her mind.

50
00:02:20,167 --> 00:02:21,600
Amanda...

51
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:28,367
You might be out of jail now.

52
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:32,100
And you might have changed
your appearance.

53
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:35,133
But you can't escape my wrath.

54
00:02:35,267 --> 00:02:40,500
I will show you the way to hell!

55
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:43,967
Yen, please tell me
you're all safe.

56
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:46,900
Rina has my mom, Auntie.

57
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:48,200
What?

58
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:52,833
Auntie, please promise me
that you will take care of Chloe

59
00:02:52,967 --> 00:02:56,100
no matter what happens.

60
00:02:56,233 --> 00:02:57,800
Yen, what are you talking about?

61
00:02:57,933 --> 00:02:59,800
Don't talk like that.

62
00:02:59,933 --> 00:03:02,467
Auntie, you have
to promise me.

63
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:05,833
What about Amanda? What's going
to happen to her?

64
00:03:05,967 --> 00:03:08,833
Angelo, my son.

65
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:11,867
I didn't get to visit you
for a while.

66
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,433
I'm here now.

67
00:03:13,567 --> 00:03:16,233
To fulfill my promise.

68
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:20,233
Finally, I can get revenge
for you.

69
00:03:23,367 --> 00:03:25,100
You're crazy!

70
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:45,100
You might not understand
how I feel.

71
00:03:45,233 --> 00:03:47,767
Because you hate my wife.

72
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:51,533
She did nothing
but make your family suffer.

73
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:56,900
But I met Rina before she turned
like this.

74
00:03:58,167 --> 00:04:00,533
She was a different person
back then.

75
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:03,100
She loves our children so much.

76
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:05,733
She's devoted to our family.

77
00:04:05,867 --> 00:04:10,133
So that's why she's changed
so much.

78
00:04:10,267 --> 00:04:13,300
She wanted revenge when
she got hurt.

79
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:17,233
But it's wrong for her
to take it out

80
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:18,500
on an innocent person.

81
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:22,100
Because my sister
did nothing wrong.

82
00:04:22,233 --> 00:04:24,500
I know.

83
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:29,633
That's why I want to
give Rina another chance.

84
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:32,133
For her to realize
that she's wrong.

85
00:04:32,267 --> 00:04:35,000
So she can ask you
for forgiveness,

86
00:04:35,133 --> 00:04:38,433
especially from Amanda and Eden.

87
00:04:38,567 --> 00:04:41,667
You love your wife so much.

88
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:48,767
I thought I could turn my back
on her after what she did.

89
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:51,500
When she kept secrets from me.

90
00:04:51,633 --> 00:04:54,000
But I can't.

91
00:04:56,033 --> 00:04:58,367
I want to see Rina again.

92
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:02,967
So I can ask her
for forgiveness.

93
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:07,733
It can only happen if she
listens to Eden and Red.

94
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:10,900
If she stops getting revenge.

95
00:05:12,267 --> 00:05:14,767
I hope she'll listen to them.

96
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:18,133
But I have a bad
feeling, Dindi.

97
00:05:18,267 --> 00:05:22,467
I feel like something unpleasant
will happen.

98
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,267
- Mom!
- Aunt Amanda!

99
00:06:03,633 --> 00:06:04,833
Get out of here!

100
00:06:04,967 --> 00:06:06,900
Go! I don't want you
to get hurt!

101
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:08,800
- Mom!
- I won't leave you here.

102
00:06:08,967 --> 00:06:10,533
- Get out of the way!
- Mom, please stop this!

103
00:06:10,667 --> 00:06:12,600
- Get out!
- You have to stop!

104
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:16,733
Aunt Amanda is innocent!

105
00:06:16,867 --> 00:06:18,067
You know, deep inside,

106
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:20,667
she's not capable
of killing Angelo.

107
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,900
The killer died.

108
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:23,933
That's why you're looking

109
00:06:24,067 --> 00:06:25,500
- for someone to blame!
- That's not true!

110
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:26,900
That's not true!

111
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:28,800
Mom! You have to stop!

112
00:06:28,933 --> 00:06:30,100
Okay?

113
00:06:30,233 --> 00:06:32,533
You made them pay for
their sins already.

114
00:06:32,667 --> 00:06:34,000
Is that not enough?

115
00:06:34,133 --> 00:06:36,367
Angelo will not like this!

116
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,433
He will understand!

117
00:06:37,567 --> 00:06:40,500
He will understand why
I'm doing this.

118
00:06:40,633 --> 00:06:41,533
Mom, no!

119
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,700
Angelo is a good person!

120
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:46,500
He won't like it if someone dies
because of him!

121
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,933
This is enough!

122
00:06:50,067 --> 00:06:52,600
- You have to stop!
- You can't be happy!

123
00:06:52,733 --> 00:06:55,333
- I can't let you be happy!
- You have to stop!

124
00:06:55,467 --> 00:06:56,533
- You have to get out of here.
- Red, let's go!

125
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,800
- Get out of here!
- Red, let's go!

126
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:07,000
I will kill you, Amanda!
I will kill you!

127
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:09,267
I will kill all of you!

128
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:20,867
Red, no! No!

129
00:07:40,467 --> 00:07:42,867
Red, no! No!

130
00:07:56,033 --> 00:07:58,300
Mom!

131
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:02,233
No, don't touch her!
Don't move her.

132
00:08:02,367 --> 00:08:03,933
Call an ambulance!

133
00:08:04,067 --> 00:08:06,100
- Don't touch her.
- Red, give me your phone.

134
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:07,833
Red, give me your phone.

135
00:08:07,967 --> 00:08:09,200
Call an ambulance.

136
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:11,433
- Let's wait for the ambulance.
- Just hang on, Mom.

137
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:13,733
We'll look for help.
Yen, hurry up!

138
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:16,967
We're at the cemetery.

139
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:20,967
Red...

140
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,700
Don't cry for me.

141
00:08:23,867 --> 00:08:25,500
I think...

142
00:08:27,533 --> 00:08:31,600
- Yen!
- I think I deserve this.

143
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:40,900
You're better off without me.

144
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:46,867
Maybe when I'm gone...

145
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:53,167
When I'm gone, you will finally
be happy.

146
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,300
Dad.

147
00:09:03,433 --> 00:09:06,100
Red, Eden.

148
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:08,900
Uncle, you should stop drinking.

149
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:20,333
Eden, I'm sorry.

150
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:23,800
I'm so sorry.

151
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:26,267
You didn't do anything wrong.

152
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,733
I did.

153
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:32,767
I didn't get to stop Rina.

154
00:09:34,233 --> 00:09:36,033
I didn't get to watch her
every move.

155
00:09:37,933 --> 00:09:41,567
I didn't have any idea
what she's been doing.

156
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:44,767
What kind of husband am I?

157
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:49,467
Dad, don't be too hard
on yourself.

158
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:54,200
Mom was determined to hide
her dealings.

159
00:09:54,333 --> 00:09:56,467
She didn't want us to find out.

160
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:02,367
But I shouldn't have condoned
her hatred for Amanda.

161
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:07,100
At the back of my mind,
I know she's innocent.

162
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:10,533
I just needed to blame somebody.

163
00:10:10,667 --> 00:10:12,933
Because it's so painful
to lose a child.

164
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:19,067
Eden, I'm sorry.

165
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:22,533
We did you wrong.

166
00:10:23,567 --> 00:10:25,033
We took you away from your mom.

167
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:27,700
And now, from your child.

168
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:33,800
Uncle, you have nothing to do
with what happened to Chloe.

169
00:10:34,633 --> 00:10:37,733
But I still need to
ask for forgiveness.

170
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,000
From you.

171
00:10:40,133 --> 00:10:41,533
From both of you.

172
00:10:42,733 --> 00:10:47,000
I'm doing it
on Rina's behalf, too.

173
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:49,467
It won't be easy

174
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:52,733
because she's hurt you
many times.

175
00:10:54,567 --> 00:11:00,000
But I hope you find it
in your heart to forgive Rina.

176
00:11:01,867 --> 00:11:03,833
Don't give up on her.

177
00:11:04,867 --> 00:11:07,567
Especially you, Red.

178
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,933
She's still your mom...

179
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:14,433
in the same way she's still
my wife.

180
00:11:19,533 --> 00:11:21,667
We need an ambulance!

181
00:11:23,167 --> 00:11:24,167
Help!

182
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:28,733
Mom! Please, Mom, no.

183
00:11:28,867 --> 00:11:31,033
Don't talk right now, okay?

184
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:34,100
We'll wait for the ambulance.
We'll talk later.

185
00:11:34,233 --> 00:11:36,067
They're on their way here, Mom.
They're on their way.

186
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:38,133
They're almost here.
Any minute now.

187
00:11:44,067 --> 00:11:48,033
Amanda, I don't care how
often you have asked

188
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:49,067
for a day off.

189
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,467
I said you can't take
a day off today.

190
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:53,433
You need to watch Angelo.

191
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:55,067
Mom, I'll be okay.

192
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,333
Let her have a day off.

193
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,433
Mom!

194
00:12:23,933 --> 00:12:25,867
Red.

195
00:12:28,067 --> 00:12:30,367
She has a lot of injuries.

196
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,733
She lost a lot of blood.

197
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:43,300
Her vital organs were damaged
when she crashed her car.

198
00:12:43,433 --> 00:12:46,133
They said they couldn't
do anything to help her.

199
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:51,767
She needs you right now.

200
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:56,267
You should stay by her side.

201
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:01,000
We've already said our goodbyes.

202
00:13:02,733 --> 00:13:05,033
She wants to talk to you.

203
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:35,900
My son's blood is on her hands!

204
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:37,800
I lost my son!

205
00:13:37,933 --> 00:13:41,400
She should go to jail
and not me!

206
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,467
I won't be surprised
if you lose your child.

207
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,333
That's what you call karma.

208
00:13:48,467 --> 00:13:49,367
You know what?

209
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:50,433
I'll pay for her coffin.

210
00:13:50,567 --> 00:13:51,633
They have a buy one
take one promo.

211
00:13:51,767 --> 00:13:54,133
You can use the other one.

212
00:13:56,133 --> 00:13:59,633
If you're here to see
your daughter,

213
00:13:59,767 --> 00:14:02,233
I'd wish she's in critical
condition.

214
00:14:02,367 --> 00:14:04,700
Or better yet, I wish she was
with my son now.

215
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,400
Remember Angelo, the kid
you murdered.

216
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:09,367
That way, I can get revenge
on you.

217
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:12,933
That's what you deserve!

218
00:14:13,067 --> 00:14:15,767
Even if you bathe with alcohol,

219
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:18,567
it won't be enough to clean
your soul!

220
00:14:20,733 --> 00:14:27,267
- Auntie!
- Stop that!

221
00:14:33,767 --> 00:14:35,800
What's going on?

222
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:47,000
How does it feel to get disowned
by your own child?

223
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:54,867
This is it, Amanda!

224
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:58,733
This will be your new home!

225
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:34,600
Amanda.

226
00:15:38,733 --> 00:15:41,233
Please, forgive me.

227
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:55,933
Forgive me, Amanda.

228
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,667
Red was right.

229
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:12,167
I looked for someone to blame.

230
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:22,433
I couldn't bear
to lose my child.

231
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:28,467
I couldn't bear to lose Angelo.

232
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,000
Amanda...

233
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:48,133
I was blinded by hatred...

234
00:16:49,167 --> 00:16:52,133
and pain.

235
00:16:56,300 --> 00:17:01,667
It hurts to lose
a child, Amanda.

236
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:04,900
It's painful.

237
00:17:08,067 --> 00:17:11,333
It still hurts now.

238
00:17:11,467 --> 00:17:15,400
I'm still hurting, Amanda.

239
00:17:20,467 --> 00:17:23,067
It's my fault, too.

240
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:26,567
It's my fault, Rina.

241
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:29,567
I didn't get to protect Angelo.

242
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:33,167
It's not your fault.

243
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:35,200
You didn't do anything wrong.

244
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:39,867
It's all my fault.

245
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:45,767
It's all my fault, Amanda.

246
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:49,167
It's all my fault.

247
00:18:01,933 --> 00:18:03,967
Amanda...

248
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:09,667
Amanda, I need to ask you
a favor.

249
00:18:14,633 --> 00:18:18,767
Take care of our children,
Amanda.

250
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,433
I will take care of them.

251
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:27,900
Promise me that you
will take care of them.

252
00:18:29,967 --> 00:18:31,633
Amanda...

253
00:18:34,367 --> 00:18:37,767
You're more deserving
to be loved

254
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:41,367
by our grandchildren.

255
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:53,500
Rina.

256
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:58,733
All your pain
will be wiped away.

257
00:19:01,367 --> 00:19:03,333
You can rest now.

258
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:16,600
Rina.

259
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:36,567
Victor, Red.

260
00:22:18,700 --> 00:22:22,100
Dad, have you chosen
a dress for mom?

261
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:32,733
I'm sorry, son.

262
00:22:32,867 --> 00:22:35,533
I failed your mom as a husband,

263
00:22:35,667 --> 00:22:38,767
just as I failed you
as a father.

264
00:22:42,033 --> 00:22:44,267
No, Dad.

265
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:48,233
I didn't get to protect your mom
against herself.

266
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:51,300
She ended up hurting you
and Eden.

267
00:22:54,367 --> 00:22:56,067
And I lost her.

268
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:59,100
She's gone now.

269
00:22:59,233 --> 00:23:03,167
I feel like I should
have died, too.

270
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:04,633
I don't deserve to be here.

271
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:06,800
- No, Dad.
- After I failed, Red.

272
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:07,833
I failed.

273
00:23:07,967 --> 00:23:10,100
No.

274
00:23:10,233 --> 00:23:12,567
Dad, I don't
want to lose you.

275
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:16,333
I can't bear to lose you.

276
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:21,067
I need you.

277
00:23:23,267 --> 00:23:25,267
Your grandchild needs you.

278
00:23:28,767 --> 00:23:31,000
And you didn't fail.

279
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:34,333
You're the only one
who's been there for me

280
00:23:34,467 --> 00:23:36,633
all these years.

281
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:39,133
You're the only person
I depend on.

282
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:44,400
When mom was unstable...

283
00:23:46,367 --> 00:23:49,067
you were there for me.

284
00:23:50,667 --> 00:23:57,467
You taught me how to be strong
and resilient.

285
00:24:02,533 --> 00:24:04,533
You taught me how
to give importance

286
00:24:04,667 --> 00:24:07,033
to the people we love.

287
00:24:08,367 --> 00:24:10,167
Red.

288
00:24:12,733 --> 00:24:15,367
So please, stay with us, Dad.

289
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:20,333
Stay with us while
we're raising Chloe.

290
00:24:21,967 --> 00:24:25,100
And your future
grandchildren.

291
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:32,967
Dad, I appreciate your guidance.

292
00:24:36,733 --> 00:24:39,300
Stay with us.

293
00:24:39,433 --> 00:24:42,633
While I'm building my own
family.

294
00:24:47,267 --> 00:24:49,333
Thank you, son.

295
00:24:49,467 --> 00:24:51,333
Thank you.

296
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:09,700
Thank you, Lucho.

297
00:25:11,100 --> 00:25:18,600
Thank you so much for loving me
and for loving my family.

298
00:25:18,733 --> 00:25:21,400
We can't take back
what happened before.

299
00:25:21,533 --> 00:25:24,867
And we can't bring back
the people we lost.

300
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:28,000
But we can still make up for it.

301
00:25:28,133 --> 00:25:29,933
While we're building
our own family.

302
00:25:30,067 --> 00:25:32,667
Mom, I'm so happy right now.

303
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,900
Because we're complete now.

304
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:39,400
You, Red, and Chloe are here.

305
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:40,667
Amanda.

306
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:41,467
Yes?

307
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:43,033
The police officers are here.

308
00:25:43,167 --> 00:25:46,200
What can I do for you?
